---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../components/PageHeader.astro';
import FaqItem from '../components/FaqItem.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="FAQs | Monarch Chihuahuas"
  description="Frequently asked questions about our puppies and our breeding practices at Monarch Chihuahuas."
  keywords="puppy faq, chihuahua questions, breeder FAQ"
>
  <PageHeader
    title="Frequently Asked Questions"
    subtitle="Find answers to common questions about our puppies and process"
  />

  <section class="faq-content">
    <div class="content-container">
      <h2>General Questions</h2>

      <FaqItem question="Are Chihuahuas a good breed?">
        <p>Chihuahuas are devoted and spirited dogs that make wonderful companions. They are loyal, intelligent, and full of personality in a tiny package. With proper training and gentle socialization, they make excellent companions for individuals, couples, and families with older children.</p>
      </FaqItem>

      <FaqItem question="Are Chihuahuas good for beginners?">
        <p>Yes! Chihuahuas are great for first-time dog owners, particularly those in apartments. They are affectionate, easy to handle, and adapt beautifully to almost any living situation. Their small size makes them easier to manage than larger breeds.</p>
      </FaqItem>

      <FaqItem question="Do Chihuahuas make good family pets?">
        <p>Absolutely — in the right setting. Chihuahuas thrive in families with older, gentle children who can respect their tiny size. They form deep bonds with everyone in the household, but they do best when handled carefully due to their delicate frame.</p>
      </FaqItem>

      <FaqItem question="Do Chihuahuas shed a lot?">
        <p>Chihuahuas are moderate shedders. Smooth-coat Chihuahuas need only a quick weekly brushing; long-coats benefit from brushing 2-3 times a week. Regular bathing every 4-6 weeks and good dental care keep them clean and fresh-smelling.</p>
      </FaqItem>

      <FaqItem question="What should I know about Chihuahua health?">
        <p>Chihuahuas are generally a robust and long-lived breed (often 14-18 years). They can be prone to dental issues, patellar luxation, and hypoglycemia in young puppies. Regular vet checkups, dental care, and a quality diet will keep your Chihuahua thriving for years.</p>
      </FaqItem>

      <h2>About Our Puppies</h2>

      <FaqItem question="What is included when I purchase a puppy?">
        <p>Each puppy comes with: current vaccinations, deworming records, a veterinary health certificate, a 1-year health guarantee, a puppy starter kit, and ongoing support from our team.</p>
      </FaqItem>

      <FaqItem question="How do I reserve a puppy?">
        <p>Contact us through our website or by message to express your interest. We'll discuss available puppies, answer your questions, and guide you through the reservation process, which typically includes a deposit to hold the puppy.</p>
      </FaqItem>

      <FaqItem question="Do you offer delivery?">
        <p>Yes! We offer both pickup and delivery options. We prefer in-person pickup so we can meet you and ensure a smooth transition, but we understand this isn't always possible. Safe air and ground delivery arrangements can be made across the United States.</p>
      </FaqItem>

      <FaqItem question="Are your puppies potty trained?">
        <p>We begin potty training and crate training with our puppies before they go to their new homes. While they won't be fully trained, they'll have a strong foundation for you to continue their training.</p>
      </FaqItem>

      <FaqItem question="What colors/patterns do you have?">
        <p>Our chihuahuas come in a wide variety of beautiful colors and patterns — fawn, cream, chocolate, black, white, blue, sable, brindle, parti, and more. Check our Available Puppies page to see current options, or contact us about upcoming litters.</p>
      </FaqItem>

      <div class="cta-box">
        <h3>Have More Questions?</h3>
        <p>We're here to help! Reach out to us with any additional questions.</p>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn">Contact Us</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .faq-content {
    padding: 4rem 1.5rem;
    background: #f8f6f3;
  }

  .content-container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #2B2018;
    margin: 2rem 0 1.5rem;
  }

  h2:first-of-type {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .cta-box {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-primary), var(--color-primary));
    color: white;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .cta-box h3 {
    color: white;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .cta-box p {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .btn {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: white;
    padding: 0.875rem 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .btn:hover {
    background: var(--color-secondary);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .faq-content {
      padding: 3rem 1rem;
    }

    h2 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
